# Security Checklist (All Code)

Apply these checks to every code change before requesting review.

## Input Validation

- [ ] All user inputs are validated (length, type, format).
- [ ] SQL injection prevented via parameterized queries/ORM.
- [ ] NoSQL injection prevented (MongoDB, Redis, etc.).
- [ ] XSS prevention: output encoding for all rendered data.

## Authentication & Authorization

- [ ] RBAC checks applied at API boundary.
- [ ] JWT tokens validated (signature, expiry, issuer).
- [ ] No hardcoded credentials or secrets in code.
- [ ] Secrets injected via environment/K8s secrets.

## Data Protection

- [ ] PII/PCI data encrypted at rest and in transit.
- [ ] Sensitive data not logged (mask in Serilog/ELK).
- [ ] GDPR compliance: data minimization, right to erasure.

## Infrastructure

- [ ] Network policies restrict pod-to-pod traffic.
- [ ] Containers run as non-root.
- [ ] Resource limits set (prevent DoS via resource exhaustion).
- [ ] Images scanned for vulnerabilities before deploy.

